         <abstract>
            <p>This article describes how the capabilities of the MacLang authoring system allow the teacher to create computer-assisted instruction that fulfills the listening needs of foreign langauge courses. Examples are given of the use of audio and video interfaces which facilitate listening comprehension.</p>
         </abstract>
